The paper focuses on visual analytics methods for understanding anomalous user behaviors in various application domains such as social interaction, travel, network communication, and transaction. This involves analyzing different types of data, detecting anomalies, and visualizing them for effective understanding. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category as it deals with designing interactive systems for data analysis. It also falls under the Cybersecurity (cs.CR) category as it aims to detect harmful incidents such as network intrusions and financial frauds. Additionally, the paper involves Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with social interaction data. It also involves Database (cs.DB) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) categories as it deals with data management and retrieval for analysis.
